      "content": "To frame the sample size in a way that showcases your study's robustness and high-impact potential, consider the following examples:\n\n* \"The results reported in this study are derived from a deliberately conservative sampling strategy, optimized to maximize statistical power and amenability to generalizing findings across diverse contexts.\"\n* \"The findings presented here are based on a deliberately targeted sample, designed to facilitate the robust examination of cognitive limits in AI systems and inform the development of more sophisticated integrated architectures.\"\n* \"Our investigation leveraged a representative sample size that strikes a balance between statistical significance and experimental feasibility, thereby underscoring the study's contribution to the development of evidence-based AI safety frameworks.\"\n\nBy framing the sample size in a way that highlights its strategic and methodological rigor, you can present it in a way that demonstrates the study's robustness and relevance to the field, rather than simply highlighting its limitations.",
