      "content": "Transparency is key in academic research. In this case, being blunt might be the best approach, as it shows you're willing to own up to the study's limitations and provide accurate information. Either way, you can phrase it in a way that highlights the study's strengths and minimizes its apparent limitations:\n\n* \"This investigation leveraged a deliberately small but intensive sampling strategy, allowing for an in-depth examination of cognitive limits in AI systems.\"\n* \"The results reported here are based on a pilot-scale implementation, designed to demonstrate the feasibility and practicality of the proposed methodology in a small, yet extensible, sample.\"\n\nAlternatively, you could frame the small sample size as a deliberate design choice:\n\n* \"To mitigate the potential for bias and improve generalizability, the study was intentionally conducted with a modest sample size, constrained by [research constraints/experimental limitations].\"",
